verbose_text: To further address the relevance of GC oscillations on NSPC proliferation, we compared the effects of oscillatory incubation with 1 x 10 -7 M and 1 x 10 -6 M CORT, which represent ~ 50 and 100% of the maximal effect of CORT on NSPC proliferation, on the expression of Sgk-1, a serine/threonine kinase involved in the inhibition of NSPC proliferation by GC [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: inhibition of NSPC proliferation by GC
